From: experintellia <280144245+experintellia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 10 Jul 2026 19:15:47 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 39/53] web-app: chat export confirm dialog (exclusions + date
 range) and viewer gap fixes
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Export Chat now opens a confirm dialog before running: it explains what
the export contains and — per review of what the app shows that an
export cannot carry — states that read receipts, full HTML e-mail
contents and webxdc app contents are not included. Optional From/Until
date fields (inclusive, local time) export only part of the history;
day markers without remaining messages are dropped, and the filtered
range applies to the viewer, messages.json, messages.txt and the
bundled media alike.

Viewer fixes for information that was already in the export data but
not shown (from the gap-hunt review):

- Vcard messages render a contact tile (avatar, name, address) from the
  embedded vcardContact instead of an empty bubble; webxdc messages say
  that app content is not part of the export instead of showing nothing.
- File tiles are download links to the bundled media/ file (with a
  'not included' note when a file exceeded the size budget); images
  link to the full-size original.
- Quotes anchor-link to their quoted message when it is in the export.
  The anchor wraps only the author line — wrapping the whole quote
  produced nested <a> elements (quoted text can contain links), which
  the HTML parser fragments into duplicated anchors.
- Failed messages show the error text (status-icon tooltip) and the
  error style independent of delivery state, like the app; messages
  that were never fully downloaded render the app's download
  placeholder instead of stub text; messages with a full HTML variant
  say so.
- Forwarded incoming group messages name the forwarder; author names
  carry the sender address as tooltip; the date tooltip includes the
  received time when it deviates; location-bearing messages show the
  location icon; .tgs Lottie stickers fall back to the file tile
  instead of a broken <img>.

New strings live in _untranslated_en.json.
